Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of 2,4,8,10-Tetraoxa-3,9-diphosphaspiro[5.5]undecane-3,9-dimethanol, r,r,rcents,rcents-tetramethyl-3,9-dioxide in Selected Solvents
Citation.sAbstract: A phosphorus-containing flame retardant 2,4,8,10-tetraoxa-3,9-diphosphaspiro[5.5]undecane-3,9-dimethanol, R,R,Rcents,Rcents-tetramethyl-3,9-dioxide (DPDM) was synthesized. The structure and the thermal stability of the compound were characterized by infrared spectroscopy (IR), nuclear magnetic resonance (1H NMR), mass spectroscopy (MS), elemental analysis, and thermogravimetric analysis. Using a static analytical method, the solubilities of DPDM in acetic acid + acetone binary mixtures, water, methanol, and ethanol were determined in the temperature range from (293.14 to 338.14) K. The solubility data were correlated with an empirical equation.
